title: For Sale:  Cold Steel Voyager X Large Tanto Folding Knife
postcontent:
The Voyager is ounce for ounce, far stronger than 99.9% of other folders. Each knife features precision made parts with a stiff spring and Cold Steel's Tri-Ad lock mechanism which is arguably the strongest, most reliable, low maintenance lock in the world! 
The thick, extra wide blades are made from Japanese AUS 8A steel and meticulously ground to a thin edge for maximum shearing potential. This thin edge also allows us to hone each blade to astounding sharpness. And, because of the high carbon content of the steel, and their near perfect heat treatment, you'll find this sharpness last a surprisingly long time. 
The Voyager Series also offers all the other latest refinements in lock-back construction including lightning quick, one-handed opening, state of the art mechanical fasteners, massively oversized pivot pins that are fully adjustable and properly hardened, and dual stainless steel pocket clips for ambidextrous carry and deployment. 
The Grivory handles feature 6061 heat treated aluminum liners for the utmost in strength and stiffness and are ergonomically designed to afford a wide array of grip options including the palm reinforced forward grip for which they are particularly well suited. 
Grivory is unparalleled as a handle material as it is considerably stronger than Zytel and, when deeply textured, offers a terrific non-slip grip. As an added bonus, it's impervious to moisture and won't crack, warp or shrink and remains remarkably resistant to abrasion or discoloration. 
As tools these lightweight, super sharp knives are appropriate in almost any environment from hunting and camping to hiking and general utility chores. They can also readily fill specialty functions such as a boat or river knife, chute knife or police/military and survival/rescue applications. 

Specifications:
Blade Length: 5.5"
Blade Thickness: 4 mm
Overall Length: 12.25"
Weight: 7.7 oz.
Steel: AUS 8

Awesome home defense weapon holing 30 rounds with fiber optic sights.

The PMR-30 is a light weight, full size pistol chambered for the flat-shooting .22Magnum cartridge (.22WMR). The PMR-30 operates on a unique hybrid blowback/locked-breech system. This operation system allows for the use of a wide variety of ammunition as it seamlessly adjusts between locked breach and blowback operation, depending on the pressure of the cartridge. It uses a double stack magazine of a new design that holds 30 rounds and fits completely in the grip of the pistol. The trigger is a crisp single action with an over-travel stop. The manual safety is a thumb activated ambidextrous safety lever (up for SAFE, down for FIRE). The slide locks back after the last shot and a manual slide lock lever is also provided. The light, crisp trigger pull and fiber optic sights make the PMR-30 ideal for target shooting and hunting small game.

TECHNICAL SPECIFICATIONS

Other features include: dual opposing extractors for reliability, heel magazine release to aid in magazine retention, dovetailed aluminum front sight, Picatinny accessory rail under the barrel, Urethane recoil buffer, captive coaxial recoil springs. PMR30 disassembles for cleaning by removal of a single pin.

title: For Sale:  Spyderco Caly 3.5 ZDP Folding Knife
postcontent:
Spyderco has several knife designs that remain steadfast year after year. What keeps people buying them over decades is their basic function but also that they’re upgraded or refreshed with new technology and materials when they become available. A prolific design in Spyderco’s line is the Calypso.
Its arrival over a decade ago as a mid-sized folder has spurned numerous variations and converted legions of knife buyers to the benefits of flat-ground, thick leaf-shaped blades. This is a workingman’s or woman’s folder founded on the premise that a comfortable, usable pocket knife is one that feels like a natural extension of your hand.
A larger, newer Bionic version of the original Calypso Jr. is the Caly3.5. The latest Calypso progeny has a three and a half inch VG-10 leaf-shaped blade that is thick at the tang, then tapering to a tip. The cutting edge is flat-ground and thin for precision and receptive cutting. Ergonomics and control were taken into the designs’ consideration and where handle and blade meet is a substantial finger choil. This is the spot where the index finger settles ergonomically leading the thumb to naturally position itself directly above on the blade’s spine. Also the spine is textured with slip resistant jimping making the knife feels like part of the hand with no sliding forward or backward while cutting. The handle has a mid-positioned back lock and a low profile wire clip, holding the folder deeply in a pocket facing tip-up.

Specifications:
Overall Length: 7.675" (194 mm)
Blade Length: 3.5" (89 mm)
Cutting Edge: 3.125" (79 mm)
Blade Thickness: 0.125" (3mm)
Blade Steel: ZDP-189
Closed Length: 4.31" (110 mm)
Hole Diameter: 0.5" (13 mm)
Weight: 3.1 oz (89 g)

title: For Sale:  Spyderco "R" Nishijin Folding Knife Glass Fiber Handle
postcontent:
The R Nishijin folder is a 2012 sprint run that is based on the original C67 “R” released by Spyderco in the 1990's that featured a skeletonized handle and blade resembling an Erector Set. The new Sprint Run “R” variant instead, has a solid blade and handle.
The blade is full-flat ground VG-10 steel with jimping perched behind the round hole on the spine, and again on the bottom finger choil, to enhance both grip and control. The back lock handle is built with skeletonized steel liners and feature Japanese Nishijin glass fiber scales. The name Nishijin references a specific weave pattern, used in the production of silk Kimono cloth. It is manufactured by weaving glass fibers (thinner than a human hair), together in a geometric pattern and then impregnating the fibers into polymer base. The outcome is a lightweight, ultra-strong handle material that has an attractive three dimension appearance.

title: For Sale:  M1C Sniper Garand Rifle W/CMP paperwork and authentication
postcontent:
Legitimate M1C Non-Import rifle purchased several years ago from CMP auction. A very desirable variant for a collector. Will include CMP certificate, and letter of authenticity from the nation’s leading M1C expert.

During the Korean War-era National Armory level rebuild program, SA-52 rebuild, this WWII sniper rifle , serial #359xxxx, was rebuilt,  and returned to regular M1 configuration, though the holes on the left side of the receiver for the screws and pins that hold the bracket are clearly visible. Finish is original. Chamber is in the white. The Muzzle Wear, or MW of this rifle is near new, just over 2, indicating this was not fired much. Barrel is dated 1-53, correct for the SA-52 rebuild timeframe which ran from approximately from July '51 to June '53. Barrel is marked correctly, SA D6535448, with date of 1 53. Wood is nice USGI walnut. Has serifed firing proof 'P' and 1/2" DAS cartouche strongly present. Operating Rod is marked D35382. Bolt is 2828712-SA, with heat lot code of W10B. Trigger housing is D28290-12-SA, with -5 SA hammer and -6 SA safety. Stamped trigger guard. Rear sight elevation is SA, windage is BME. Gas cylinder is wide base with good original finish, lock is WWII type. Screw is late, P followed by octogon symbol. Front sight is SA with late type screw. Early follower. Other parts not mentioned are late type.

Sale includes an original USGI replacement parkerized receiver bracket (scope base), though price reflects the value of the rifle only. 

Happy to provide more info on request to serious enquirer's. Will be happy to send to your FFL once payment is received and cleared.

 I would consider a partial trade plus cash of a good AR-15 rifle by Windham Weaponry, Colt 6920 or 6720 or other Colt, Armalite, or an older Colt SP1. Please don't hesitate to ask if you have more questions or would like to see more pictures. Thank you.
